---
import Page from '../../layouts/Page.astro'
---
<Page
  title="Security"
  label="Legal"
  hero="Security"
  sub="How we keep your data and your communities safe."
  description="Krenla's security practices — encryption, authentication, infrastructure, and responsible disclosure."
>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M10 2L4 5v6c0 3.5 2.6 6.7 6 7.4 3.4-.7 6-3.9 6-7.4V5L10 2Z" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>End-to-end encryption</h3>
      <p>All direct messages are end-to-end encrypted. Even Krenla cannot read them.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><rect x="5" y="9" width="10" height="8" rx="2" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M7 9V6a3 3 0 0 1 6 0v3" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Two-factor authentication</h3>
      <p>2FA via authenticator app or hardware key. Mandatory for community owners on the Community plan.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><circle cx="10" cy="10" r="7" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.5"/><path d="M10 6v4l3 2" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Transport security</h3>
      <p>All connections use TLS 1.3. HSTS enforced. Certificate pinning on mobile apps.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-ic">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none"><path d="M4 10h12M10 4v12" stroke="rgba(157,130,255,.9)" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
      <p>Hosted on EU-based infrastructure. Data never leaves the European Economic Area. Daily encrypted backups with 30-day retention.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="prose">
    <h2>Responsible disclosure</h2>
    <p>If you discover a security vulnerability in Krenla, we want to hear from you. Please report it to <a href="mailto:security@krenla.com">security@krenla.com</a> before disclosing it publicly. We'll acknowledge your report within 24 hours and aim to resolve confirmed vulnerabilities within 30 days.</p>
    <p>We don't take legal action against researchers who discover and responsibly disclose vulnerabilities in good faith.</p>

    <h2>Bug bounty</h2>
    <p>We operate a private bug bounty program. If you've reported a valid vulnerability and want to be considered for a bounty, mention it in your report. Severity and scope determine the reward.</p>

    <h2>Incident response</h2>
    <p>In the event of a data breach affecting personal data, we will notify affected users and relevant authorities within 72 hours, as required by GDPR. We'll be transparent about what happened, what data was affected, and what we're doing to fix it.</p>

    <h2>Compliance</h2>
    <p>Krenla is GDPR-compliant. We conduct annual third-party security audits. For enterprise compliance documentation, contact <a href="mailto:security@krenla.com">security@krenla.com</a>.</p>
  </div>
</Page>
